<title>BRAZIL: Brazil Cenbank workers to begin stoppages Thurs.</title>
<headline>Brazil Cenbank workers to begin stoppages Thurs.</headline>
<dateline>BRASILIA 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Employees of Brazil's Central Bank will begin a series of stoppages on Thursday as part of an ongoing labor dispute, but their actions are unlikely to affect trading, a union leader said.</p>
<p>Staff in Brasilia and other regional offices will stop work at 1400 local/1700 GMT, but the bank was not likely to be shut down by the stoppages, said Paulo Roberto de Castro, president of a Central Bank employees' union.</p>
<p>The union is demanding alterations in the classification of the bank's staff, which would entitle them to different treatment under Brazil's labor laws.</p>
<p>-- William Schomberg, Brasilia newsroom 5561 2230358</p>
